text=:Category: Varia%0a:Expansion: Universal Evolutionary Sequence for Color Vocabulary%0a:Author: JoshuaC%0a:Original: [[Articles.TheColorNamingDebate|TheColorNamingDebate]] %0a:OriginalAuthor: [[Profiles.kevinx|kevinx]]%0a:Section: F%0a:Completed: 07.05.2021 - 17:50%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeExpansion:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a%0a%25red%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210512-125214-370020#%0a* [-12.05.2021 - 05:52-] || TA_mason marked as complete%0a#foxend 210512-125214-370020#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25red%25 '''Comments to student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aAdding on to the color naming debate, there is a theory, proposed by William Gladstone and Lazarus Geiger in the 1800s, that speakers of ancient written languages did not develop or come up with terms for the colors at the same time, and that there was a universal evolutionary sequence in which color vocabulary evolved.%0a%0aFor example, they pointed to the fact that ancient Greek texts such as Homer’s The Odyssey did not contain the color blue. Instead, descriptions such as “wine-dark sea” were used to describe traditionally blue objects such as the sea. Gladstone and Geiger argued that this was because the term “blue” did not exist in Homer’s time. %0a%0aAnother example is in the development of color terms in Chinese, where the word “靑” was used to describe a whole range of colors from light green to deep blue, before modern terms “藍” and “綠” were introduced to describe blue and green respectively. %0a%0aWhile this does not necessarily mean that the Chinese people or Greek people perceived colors differently from us in ancient times, it is an interesting phenomenon that seems to be repeated in certain cultures around the world.%0a%0aReferences:%0a%0ahttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linguistic_relativity_and_the_color_naming_debate%0a%0ahttps://oxbridgeapplications.com/kyc/what-colour-is-the-sky/%0a%0ahttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue%25E2%2580%2593green_distinction_in_language%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:Category:)%0a#foxbegin 210512-000938-693170#%0a!!Backup interface%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeExpansion:)%0a#foxend 210512-000938-693170#%0a(:GradedBy: TA_mason:)
